obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10904)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10904&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Oil Industry (Development) Act, 1974.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10905)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10905&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "assistance" means assistance rendered under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Oil Industry Development Board established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) "court" means the High Court or the Court of Judicial Commissioner within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction the defendant or respondent carries on the whole or a substantial part of his`
  line `business, and where the Central Government has, by notification in the Official Gazette, and subject`
  line `to such restrictions, limitations and conditions, as it thinks fit, empowered any court of civil`
  line `jurisdiction subordinate to the High Court or, as the case may be, the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner, to exercise all or any of the powers conferred by this Act, such court;`
  line
  line `(e) "crude oil" means petroleum in its natural state before it is refined or otherwise treated but`
  line `from which water and foreign substances have been extracted;`
  line
  line `(f) "fertilisers" means such oilbased chemical compounds which when employed in agriculture`
  line `provide either single or multiple plant nutrients in any one or more of the forms of nitrogen,`
  line `phosphorus and potash;`
  line
  line `(g) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(h) "mineral oil" includes petroleum and natural gas;`
  line
  line `(i) "natural gas" means gas consisting primarily of hydrocarbons obtained from oil wells or gas`
  line wells;
  line
  line `(j) "oil industrial concern" means any company, corporation or co-operative society, which is`
  line `engaged or which is to engage in any activity referred to in clause (k);`
  line
  line `(k) "oil industry" includes all activities by way of prospecting or exploring for or production of`
  line `mineral oil, refining, processing, transportation, storage, handling, and marketing, of mineral oil,`
  line `production and marketing of all products, down-stream of an oil refinery and the production of`
  line `fertilisers and petro-chemicals and all activities directly or indirectly connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(l) "petro-chemicals" means chemicals, whether organic or inorganic, derived from petroleum`
  line `including crude oil, natural gas, condensates, refined petroleum fractions and refinery gases;`
  line
  line `(m) "petroleum product" means any commodity made from petroleum or natural gas and includes`
  line `refined crude oil, processed crude petroleum, residuum from crude petroleum cracking stock,`
  line `uncracked fuel oil, fuel oil, treated crude oil residuum, casing head gasoline, natural gas gasoline, naphtha, distillate gasoline, kerosene, bitumen, asphalt and tar, waste oil, blended gasoline,`
  line `lubricating oil, blends or mixture of oil with one or more liquid products or by-products derived from`
  line `oil or gas and blends or mixtures of two or more liquid products or by-products derived from oil`
  line `condensate and gas or petroleum hydrocarbons not specified hereinbefore;`
  line
  line `(n) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10906)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10906&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `for the purposes of this Act a Board to be called the Oil Industry Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) not more than three members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the`
  line `Ministry or Ministries of the Central Government dealing with petroleum and chemicals;`
  line
  line `(b) two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the Ministry of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with finance;`
  line
  line `(c) not more than five members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the`
  line `Corporations, being Corporations owned or controlled by the Central Government, engaged in`
  line `activities referred to in clause (k) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(d) two members of whom one shall be appointed by the Central Government from amongst`
  line `persons who, in the opinion of that Government, have special knowledge or experience of oil industry`
  line `and the other shall be appointed by that Government to represent labour employed in the oil industry;`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary to the Board, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall appoint the Chairman of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of the members of the Board (other than the members appointed by virtue of`
  line `office) and the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of`
  line `their functions by, the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Board may constitute`
  line `Standing Committees or ad hoc Committees for exercising any power or discharging any duty of the`
  line `Board or for inquiring into, reporting and advising on, any matter which the Board may refer to them:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Standing Committee shall consist exclusively of members of the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) No act or proceeding of the Board or of any Committee constituted under sub-section (6) shall be`
  line `invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board or such Committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board or such`
  line `Committee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or such Committee not affecting the merits of`
  line `the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10907)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10907&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every person appointed as a whole-time member of the`
  line `Board shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and such conditions of service in respect of leave,`
  line `pension, provident fund and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government`
  line `and the other members of the Board and such of the members of any ad hoc Committee constituted under sub-section (6) of section 3 as are not members of the Board shall be entitled to such allowances, if any,`
  line `and such other conditions of service, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10908)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Secretary, officers, consultants and employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10908&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall appoint a Secretary to the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to rules made in this behalf, the Secretary shall exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `duties as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and such conditions of service in`
  line `respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Board may appoint such`
  line `consultants as may be necessary for the performance of its functions on such terms and conditions as it`
  line `may determine from time to time.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Board may appoint such`
  line `other officers and employees as may be necessary for the performance of its functions and pay them such`
  line `salaries and allowances as it may determine from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10909)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10909&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder,`
  line `the Board shall render, in such manner, to such extent and on such terms and conditions as it may deem`
  line `fit, financial and other assistance for the promotion of all such measures as are, in its opinion, conducive`
  line `to the development of oil industry.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board may render`
  line `assistance under that sub-section by`
  line
  line `(a) making grants or advancing loans to any oil industrial concern or other person who is engaged`
  line `or is to engage in any activity referred to in clause (k) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) guaranteeing on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon loans raised by any oil`
  line `industrial concern or other person which are repayable within a period not exceeding twenty-five`
  line `years and are floated in the market or loans raised by an oil industrial concern or other person from`
  line `any bank which is a scheduled bank, or a State co-operative bank, as defined in the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(c) guaranteeing on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon deferred payments due`
  line `from any oil industrial concern or other person in connection with import of capital goods from`
  line `outside India or in connection with purchase of capital goods within India by such concern or other`
  line person;
  line
  line `(d) guaranteeing on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon loans raised from, or credit`
  line `arrangements made with, any bank or financial institution in any country outside India by any oil`
  line `industrial concern or other person in foreign currency:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such guarantee shall be given without the prior approval of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) underwriting the issue of stock, shares, bonds or debentures by any oil industrial concern and`
  line `retaining as part of its assets any stock, shares, bonds or debentures which it may have to take up in`
  line `fulfilment of its obligations thereto;`
  line
  line `(f) acting as agent for the Central Government or, with its approval, for any overseas financial`
  line `organisation or credit agency in the transaction of anybusiness with any oil industrial concern in`
  line `respect of loans or advances granted, or debentures subscribed by the Central Government or such`
  line `organisation or agency;`
  line
  line `(g) subscribing to the stock or shares of any oil industrial concern;`
  line
  line `(h) subscribing to the debentures of any oil industrial concern repayable within a period not`
  line `exceeding twenty-five years from the date on which they are subscribed to:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to preclude the Board from`
  line `subscribing to the debentures of any oil industrial concern, the amounts outstanding thereon may be`
  line `convertible at the option of the Board into stock or shares of that concern within the period the`
  line `debentures are repayable.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- In this clause, the expression "amounts outstanding thereon" used in relation to`
  line `any loan or advance shall mean the principal, interest and other charges payable on such loan or`
  line `advance as at the time when the amounts are sought to be converted into stock or shares.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the measures for the`
  line `promotion of which the Board may render assistance under that sub-section may include measures for or`
  line `by way of--`
  line
  line `(a) prospecting for and exploration of mineral oil within India (including the continental shelf`
  line `thereof) or outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) the establishment of facilities for production, handling, storage and transport of crude oil;`
  line
  line `(c) refining and marketing of petroleum and petroleum products;`
  line
  line `(d) the manufacture and marketing of petro-chemicals and fertilisers;`
  line
  line `(e) scientific, technological and economic research which could be, directly or indirectly, useful`
  line `to oil industry;`
  line
  line `(f) experimental or pilot studies in any field of oil industry;`
  line
  line `(g) training of personnel, whether in India or outside, engaged or to be engaged in any field of oil`
  line `industry, and`
  line
  line `such other measures as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may charge such fees or receive such commission as it may deem appropriate for any`
  line `services rendered by it in the exercise of its functions.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may transfer for consideration any instrument relating to loans or advances granted by`
  line `it to any oil industrial concern or other person.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may do all such things as may be incidental to or consequential upon the discharge of`
  line `its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10910)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Principles and conditions of assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10910&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before rendering any assistance to any oil industrial`
  line `concern or other person, the Board shall have regard to such directions as the Central Government may`
  line `issue in this behalf and shall satisfy itself that--`
  line
  line `(a) such assistance is not contrary to such directions; and`
  line
  line `(b) such assistance is necessary as a matter of priority in the interests of the development of oil`
  line industry.
  line
  line `(2) In rendering any assistance to any oil industrial concern or other person, the Board shall impose`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed and may also impose such additional conditions as it may think`
  line `necessary or expedient for protecting the interests of the Board and for securing that the assistance`
  line `rendered by it is put to the best use by such concern or other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10911)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10911&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any agreement`
  line `to the contrary, the Board may, by notice in writing, require any oil industrial concern or other person to`
  line `which or to whom it has rendered any assistance to discharge forthwith in full its or his liabilities to the`
  line Board--
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Board that false or misleading information in any material particulars was`
  line `given in the application for such assistance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the concern or other person has failed to comply with the terms of its or his contract with`
  line `the Board in the matter of such assistance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the concern or other person is unable to pay its or his`
  line `debts or that proceedings for liquidation or in insolvency may be commenced in respect of such`
  line `concern or person; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the Board as security is not`
  line `insured and kept insured by the concern or other person to the satisfaction of the Board; or`
  line `depreciates in value to such an extent that, in the opinion of the Board, further security to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Board should be given and such security is not given; or`
  line
  line `(e) if, without the permission of the Board, any machinery, plant or other equipment (whether or`
  line `not forming part of the security), is removed from the premises of the concern or other person without`
  line `being replaced; or`
  line
  line `(f) if for any reason it is necessary to protect the interests of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10912)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Special provisions for enforcement of claims by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10912&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an oil industrial`
  line `concern or other person, in breach of any agreement, makes any default in repayment of any loan or`
  line `advance or any instalment thereof or in meeting its or his obligations in relation to any other assistance`
  line `rendered by the Board or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of the agreement with the Board or`
  line `where the Board requires an oil industrial concern or other person to make immediate repayment of any`
  line `loan or advance and the concern or other person fails to make such repayment, then, without prejudice to`
  line `the provisions of section 69 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), any officer of the Board`
  line `generally or specially authorised by the Board in this behalf may apply to the court for one or more of the`
  line `following reliefs, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for an order for the sale of the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the`
  line `Board as security for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) for an ad interim injunction where there is apprehension of the machinery or the equipment`
  line `being removed from the premises of the oil industrial concern or other person without the permission`
  line `of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an oil industrial concern, for transferring the management of the concern to the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall state the nature and extent of the liability of the oil`
  line `industrial concern or other person to the Board, the ground on which it is made and such other particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) When the application is for the relief mentioned in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `court shall pass an ad interim order attaching the property or so much of the property of the oil industrial`
  line `concern or other person as would on being sold realise in the estimation of the court an amount equivalent`
  line `in value to the outstanding liability of the concern or other person to the Board together with costs of the`
  line `proceedings taken under this section with or without an ad interim injunction restraining the oil industrial`
  line `concern or other person from transferring or removing any machinery or equipment.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the application is for the relief mentioned in clause (c) of sub-section (1), the court shall`
  line `grant an ad interim injunction restraining the oil industrial concern from transferring or removing its`
  line `machinery and equipment and issue a notice calling upon the concern to show cause on a date to be`
  line `specified in the notice why the management of the concern should not be transferred to the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Before passing any order under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), the court may, if it thinks fit,`
  line `examine the officer making the application.`
  line
  line `(6) At the same time as it passed an order under sub-section (3), the court shall issue to the oil`
  line `industrial concern or other person a notice accompanied by copies of the order, the application and the`
  line `evidence, if any, recorded by it, calling upon the concern or other person to show cause on a date to be`
  line `specified in the notice why the ad interim order of attachment should not be made absolute or the`
  line `injunction confirmed.`
  line
  line `(7) If no cause is shown before the date specified in the notice under sub-sections (4) and (6), the`
  line `court shall forthwith make the ad interim order absolute and direct the sale of the attached property or`
  line `transfer the management of the oil industrial concern to the Board or confirm the injunction.`
  line
  line `(8) If cause is shown, the court shall proceed to investigate the claim of the Board and the provisions`
  line `of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) shall, so far as may be, apply to such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(9) On an investigation made under sub-section (8), the court shall pass an order--`
  line
  line `(a) confirming the order of attachment and directing the sale of the attached property, or`
  line
  line `(b) varying the order of attachment so as to release a portion of the property from attachment and`
  line `directing the sale of the remainder of the attached property, or`
  line
  line `(c) releasing the property from attachment, if it is satisfied that it is not necessary in the interests`
  line `of the Board, or`
  line
  line `(d) confirming or dissolving the injunction, or`
  line
  line `(e) transferring the management of the oil industrial concern to the Board or rejecting the claim`
  line `made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that when making any order under clause (c), the court may make such other orders as it`
  line `thinks necessary to protect the interests of the Board, and, may apportion the costs of the proceedings in`
  line `such manner as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that unless the Board intimates the court that it will not appeal against any order`
  line `releasing any property from attachment, such order shall not be given effect to until the expiry of the`
  line `period fixed under sub-section (12) within which an appeal may be preferred, or if an appeal is preferred,`
  line `unless the court empowered to hear appeals from the decisions of the said court otherwise directs, until`
  line `the appeal is disposed of.`
  line
  line `(10) An order of attachment or sale of property shall be carried into effect, as far as may be`
  line `practicable, in the manner provided in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the attachment`
  line `or sale of property in execution of a decree, as if the Board were the decree-holder.`
  line
  line `(11) An order under this section transferring the management of an oil industrial concern to the Board`
  line `shall be carried into effect, as far as may be practicable, in the manner provided in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the possession of immovable property or the delivery of movable`
  line `property in execution of a decree, as if the Board were the decree-holder.`
  line
  line `(12) Any party aggrieved by an order under sub-section (7) or sub-section (9) may, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of the order, appeal to the court empowered to hear appeals from the decisions of the court`
  line `which passed the order and the appellate court may after hearing the parties pass such orders as it thinks`
  line proper.
  line
  line `(13) Nothing in this section shall be construed, where proceedings for liquidation or in insolvency in`
  line `respect of the oil industrial concern or other person have commenced before an application is made under`
  line `sub-section (1) as giving to the Board any preference over the other creditors of the concern or other`
  line `person not conferred on it by any other law.`
  line
  line `(14) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any court competent to grant an ad interim`
  line `injunction under this section shall also have the power to appoint a receiver and to exercise all other`
  line `powers incidental thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10913)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Board to appoint Directors of oil industrial concern.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10913&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When the management of an`
  line `oil industrial concern is taken over by the Board, the Board may, by order notified in the Official Gazette,`
  line `appoint as many persons as it thinks fit to be the Directors of that concern and nothing in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or in any law or instrument relating to the concern, in so far as it makes, in relation`
  line `to a Director, any provision for the holding of any share qualification, age limit, restrictions on the`
  line `number of directorships, retirement by rotation or removal from office shall apply to any Director`
  line `appointed by the Board under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10914)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Effect of notified order appointing Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10914&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `On the issue of a notified order under section`
  line 10--
  line
  line `(a) all persons holding office as Director of the oil industrial concern or in charge of the`
  line `management of such concern immediately before the issue of the notified order shall be deemed to`
  line `have vacated their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) the Directors appointed under section 10 shall take such steps as may be necessary to take into`
  line `their custody or under their control the property, effects and actionable claims to which the oil`
  line `industrial concern is, or appears to be, entitled and all the property and effects of the concern shall be`
  line `deemed to be in the custody of the Directors as from the date of the notified order;`
  line
  line `(c) the Directors appointed under section 10 shall for all purposes be the Directors of the oil`
  line `industrial concern duly constituted under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and shall alone be`
  line `entitled to exercise all the powers of the Directors of the concern, whether such powers are derived`
  line `from the said Act or from the memorandum or articles of association of the concern or from any other`
  line source.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10915)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers and duties of the Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10915&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the control of the Board, the Directors`
  line `appointed under section 10 shall take such steps as may be necessary for the purpose of efficiently`
  line `managing the business of the oil industrial concern and shall exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers vested in them under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Directors appointed under section 10 may, with the previous approval of the Board, make an application`
  line `to a court for the purpose of cancelling or varying any contract or agreement entered into, at any`
  line `timebefore the issue of the notified order under section 10, between the oil industrial concern and any`
  line `other person and the court may, if satisfied after due inquiry that such contract or agreement had been`
  line `entered into in bad faith and is detrimental to the interests of the concern, make an order cancelling or`
  line `varying (either unconditionally or subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose) that contract or`
  line `agreement and the contract or agreement shall accordingly stand cancelled or, as the case may be, have`
  line `effect as so varied.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10916)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `No right to compensation for loss of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10916&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, no Director or other person in charge of the management of an oil`
  line `industrial concern immediately before the issue of a notified order under section 10 in respect of such`
  line `concern shall be entitled to any compensation for the loss of office or for the premature termination under`
  line `this Act of the contract entitling him to be in charge of such management.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any Director or other person referred`
  line `to therein to recover from the oil industrial concern moneys recoverable otherwise than by way of such`
  line compensation.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10917)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Application of Act 1 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10917&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the management of an oil industrial concern, being a`
  line `company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956, is taken over by the Board, then, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the said Act or in the memorandum or articles of association of such concern,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall not be lawful for the shareholders of such concern or any other person to nominate or`
  line `appoint any person to be a Director of such concern;`
  line
  line `(b) no resolution passed at any meeting of the shareholders of such concern shall be given effect`
  line `to unless approved by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) no proceeding for the winding up of such concern or for the appointment of a receiver in`
  line `respect thereof shall lie in any court, except with the consent of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (1) and to the other provisions contained in this`
  line `Act and subject to such other exceptions, restrictions and limitations, if any, as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `shall continue to apply to such concern in the same manner as it applied thereto before the issue of the`
  line `notified order under section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10918)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duties of excise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10918&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be levied and collected, as a cess for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `on every item specified in column 2 of the Schedule, which is produced in India (including the`
  line `continental shelf thereof) and--`
  line
  line `(a) removed to a refinery or factory; or`
  line
  line `(b) transferred by the person by whom such item is produced to another person,`
  line
  line `a duty of excise at such rate not exceeding the rate set forth in the corresponding entry in column 3 of the`
  line `Schedule, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Central Government specifies by such notification the rate of the duty of`
  line `excise in respect of crude oil (being an item specified in the Schedule) the duty of excise on crude oil`
  line `under this sub-section shall be levied and collected at the rate of rupees sixty per tonne.`
  line
  line `(2) Every duty of excise leviable under sub-section (1) on any item shall be payable by the person by`
  line `whom such item is produced, and in the case of crude oil, the duty of excise shall be collected on the`
  line `quantity received in a refinery.`
  line
  line `(3) The duties of excise under sub-section (1) on the items specified in the Schedule shall be in`
  line `addition to any cess or duty leviable on those items under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Central Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, including those relating to refunds and exemptions from duties shall, as far as may be, apply`
  line `in relation to the levy and collection of duties of excise leviable under this section and for this purpose the`
  line `provisions of that Act shall have effect as if that Act provided for the levy of duties of excise on all items`
  line `specified in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (10919)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Crediting of proceeds of duty to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10919&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of the duties of`
  line `excise levied under section 15 shall first be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India and the Central`
  line `Government may, if Parliament by appropriation made by law in this behalf, so provides, pay to the`
  line `Board from time to time, from out of such proceeds, after deducting the expenses of collection, such sums`
  line `of money as it may think fit for being utilised exclusively for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10920)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10920&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may also, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Board by way of grants or loans such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10921)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Oil Industry Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 140 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10921&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a Fund to be called the Oil`
  line `Industry Development Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) any sums of money paid under section 16 or section 17;`
  line
  line `(b) any grants that may be made by any person or institution for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any borrowings by the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) the sums, if any, realised by the Board in carrying out its functions or in the administration of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the salaries, allowances, honoraria and other remuneration of the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Board and of the advisers, consultants or other agencies whose services are`
  line `availed of by the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the other administrative expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) for rendering assistance under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) for repayment of any loans taken by the Board or for meeting other liabilities under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(e) for meeting any expenditure incurred by any Central Public Sector Undertaking in the oil and gas sector, on behalf of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) for meeting expenditure on any scheme or activity by the Central Government relating to oil and gas sector.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (10922)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to borrow.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10922&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, the Board shall have the`
  line `power to borrow on the security of the Oil Industry Development Fund or any other asset for carrying out`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (10923)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10923&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the profit and loss account and the balance-sheet`
  line `in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (10924)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to require persons engaged in oil industry to maintain and produce books, accounts and records relating to business and inspection thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10924&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette, require all persons engaged in oil industry or any class of such persons--`
  line
  line `(a) to maintain such books, accounts and records relating to their business as may be specified in`
  line `the order;`
  line
  line `(b) to produce such books, accounts and records for inspection and to furnish such information`
  line `relating thereto to such officer or authority and at such times or in such circumstances as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (10925)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Directions by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=10925&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (29440)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 23
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29440&sectionno=22A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `[Exemption from liability to pay income-tax.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 2002 (20 of 2002),`
  line `s. 159 (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (29441)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title Penalties
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29441&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) being required under this Act to produce any books, accounts or records or furnish any`
  line `information, fails to produce such books, accounts or records or fails to furnish such information or`
  line `furnishes information which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false, or does not`
  line `believe to be true; or`
  line
  line `(b) obstructs any member or any officer or other employee of the Board or any person authorized`
  line `in this behalf by the Central Government or by the Board in the exercise of any power conferred or in`
  line `the discharge of any duty imposed on him by or under this Act, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (29442)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Other penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29442&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder (other than the provisions for the`
  line `contravention of which section 23 applies), shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (29443)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29443&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (29444)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29444&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (29445)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Previous sanction of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29445&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (29446)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29446&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the Board or any committee constituted by the Board or any`
  line `member of the Board or of such committee or any officer or other employee of the Central Government`
  line `or of the Board or any agent of or any other person authorised by the Central Government or the Board,`
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (29447)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Dissolution of the Board`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29447&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, if satisfied that it is necessary so`
  line `to do in the public interest, direct by notification in the Official Gazette that the Board shall be dissolved`
  line `from such date and for such period as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Board is dissolved under the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members, notwithstanding that their term of office has not expired, shall, from the date of`
  line `dissolution, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all funds and other properties vested in the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, vest`
  line `in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Board shall be re-constituted in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (29448)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29448&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect, notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (29449)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936&sectionId=29449&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00002_197447_1517807320936
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office and other conditions of service of members, the manner of filling vacancies`
  line `among and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which shall be performed by the Secretary`
  line `to the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances in which and the authority by which a member may be removed;`
  line
  line `(d) the holding of minimum number of meetings of the Board every year;`
  line
  line `(e) the convening of meetings of the Board and of its committees, the procedure to be followed at`
  line `the meetings of the Board and of its committees for the conduct of business and the number of`
  line `members which shall form quorum at a meeting;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance by the Board of records of business transacted by the Board and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) the powers of the Board, its Chairman and other members, Secretary and committees of the`
  line `Board with respect to the incurring of expenditure;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions subject to which the Board may incur expenditure outside India;`
  line
  line `(i) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Board and the authority`
  line `by which the estimates are to be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner in which the accounts should be kept by the Board;`
  line
  line `(k) the custody and investment of the funds of the Board;`
  line
  line `(l) the conditions to be observed by the Board in borrowing money;`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions subject to which and the manner in which contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(n) the delegation to the Chairman, Secretary or members or officers of the Board of any of the`
  line `powers and duties of the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) the additional measures for the promotion of which the Board may render assistance;`
  line
  line `(p) the remuneration and other allowances payable to the person or persons referred to in clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (2) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(q) the fees which the Board may charge for any assistance or services rendered by it under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(r) the staff which may be employed by the Board and the pay and allowances and leave and`
  line `other conditions of service of officers (other than those appointed by the Central Government) and`
  line `other employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(s) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed or provided for by rules under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament. while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
